Heat the oil in a heavy, 6-quart saucepan or Dutch oven. Add the onions and garlic and saute until golden, stirring constantly, about 5 minutes. Stir in the water, tomatoes, beans, and pepper. Bring to a boil over high heat; reduce heat to low, cover, and simmer Â½ hours. Add the mint and salt; simmer 15 minutes longer or until beans are tender.